column3: Returns indicative of living organisms moving in groups or schools (e.g., pods, shoals, coordinated movement, dispersal when startled).
Metallic resonance, twisted or jagged structures, debris fields, or echoes consistent with man-made objects and wreckage.
Stable contours and formations such as ridges, caverns, dunes, rock lattices, layered deposits, or dome-like/maze-like natural patterns.
Acoustic artifacts including rhythmic or mechanical pulses, static bursts, harmonic tones, or refraction leading to unpredictable bounces.
Anomalous or ambiguous readings lacking a clear biological, artificial, or geological explanation (e.g., sudden voids, persistent unexplained signals or formations).
